{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"misty-creatable-mallard","description":"## Reproduction Steps\n1. Fresh git worktree of rebar (no .rebar/ directory) with the shared ticket store reachable (.tickets-tracker via the common .git).\n2. `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_llm_disposition_plumbing.py::test_degraded_code_review_carries_disposition -q`\n3. The autouse `_no_repo_root_leaks` fixture ERRORs at teardown: `Test leaked new entries into REPO_ROOT: ['.rebar', '.rebar/current_session_log']`.\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n- Expected: unit tests never touch the real store or the repo root; the suite passes in a fresh worktree.\n- Actual: `_degraded_code_review_verdict` -> `rebar.llm.failure.log_degrade` -> `rebar.append_session_log` performs a REAL store write (creates a session_log ticket in the shared tickets branch) and creates the `.rebar/current_session_log` pointer in the repo root. In CI the store is unreachable so the swallowed exception masks it; in a developer worktree it both fails the suite (leak fixture) and pollutes the shared store with test session-log tickets. Found while landing ticket 70c8-423e-e4c1-4d86 (pre-existing: reproduces on pristine origin/main).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] tests/unit/test_llm_disposition_plumbing.py degraded-verdict tests stub or isolate `failure.log_degrade` (or the tests run under an isolated REBAR store root) so no real store write occurs.\n- [ ] The full unit suite passes in a fresh worktree whose repo root has no .rebar/ directory.\n- [ ] No session_log ticket is created in the store by running the unit suite.","id":"d9aa-1b5b-4c64-4267","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"log_degrade in unit tests writes to the real ticket store (leaks .rebar/current_session_log into fresh worktrees)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783836664374391001,"uuid":"08929d3f-66fe-4701-89be-bbb37b758b63"}